Date: 0/0/1928
Source: Dawn Beloved
Author: DEVANNY
Vol / Page: 169
Edition:
Quote: (coalmining) ... drives were broken off at right angles to [the dip heading] at distances of two chains apart ; thus forming pillars on either side of the dip, two chains square. These drives were called main levels. The bords were driven about two chains off the dip, and the `stenton' would be driven from the lower level to the one above.
Notes:

