Date: 0/0/1967
Source: West Coast Gold Rushes
Author: MAY
Vol / Page: 526
Edition: 1962
Quote: DRIVE: a horizontal excavation. As a verb (`driving') to make a horizontal excavation. `Drive' and `tunnel' were used interchangeably, but properly one tunnelled into a lead or reef and then commenced to `drive' along it.
Notes:

